WHO WE ARE

We are Power Factors, developer of the world’s leading cloud platform for renewable energy companies. Our SaaS platform, DRIVE, is used to manage over 25 Gigawatts of renewable energy across the planet (enough to power approximately 1.5 million homes). We’re tackling one of the world’s most important challenges in making renewable energy the world’s leading source of power by driving down the cost to operate wind and solar power plants. Our company is going through accelerated growth fueled by the unprecedented transition to clean, renewable energy.

The DRIVE platform continues to extend throughout the renewable energy market. Our platform collects millions of IoT and other data points, cleanses the data, detects occurring issues, identifies leading indicators to predict future issues, and adds a full advanced analytic capability on top of this rich, high value dataset. In addition to issue detection and analytics, DRIVE adds the toolsets needs to take analytic insights to action such as case management and work order management.

To our customers, we deliver excellent customer service and a high value system of engagement that provides the results they are looking for: lower operations costs and higher output from their renewable energy power plants. We are an agile development company, big enough to make an impact, but small enough to move quickly to execute in a growing industry and take advantage of rapidly evolving technology. To our employees, we provide a culture that values respect, teamwork, transparency, and achievement.

THE ROLE

As a Data Scientist on the Power Factors’ Solar Advanced Analytics team, you will investigate analytical and characterization questions across all aspects of photovoltaics performance, operations, management and reporting. Be prepared to explore a wide variety of data science tool sets to extract information from diverse data sets. The best candidates will be curious and willing to continually take on new challenges and opportunities to learn (new programing languages, techniques, technologies). You will provide well defined solutions to our Software Development team for implementation in Power Factors’ Drive platform.

In this role, you will be reporting to the Technical Director, Solar and you will be an active member of a team composed of passionate and highly qualified professionals that aims at changing the energy landscape.


YOUR RESPONSIBILITIES
Collaborate with other members of the Solar Data Science team to explore analytical problems and solutions;
Work independently to investigate and develop specific characterization techniques;
Integrate and maintain targeted characterizations in the broader context of applied, predictive and prescriptive analytics;
Ensure that analytics are robust and resilient in a production environment with diverse assets and variable data quality;
Write sophisticated machine learning and data analysis code in Python, R or MATLAB;
Work closely with other Solar Data Scientists and Software Engineering Team to maintain coding standards and revision control to facilitate seamless integration of new capabilities;
Work with Data Engineers on data quality assessment, data cleansing and analytics;
Collaborate with Product Managers to understand requirements and use cases;
Develop, verify and validate analytics to address customer needs and requirements;
Communicate effectively with people at all levels of the organization. Our data scientists regularly share complex insights with all kinds of people;
Continuously strive to efficiently deliver actionable information to Power Factors’ customers. You will interact directly with internal and external Performance Engineers to design solutions that help them solve real world problems and drive value.


QUALIFICATIONS


Master’s degree in Statistics, Mathematics, in Computer Science, or in a related field;
Minimum 5 years of relevant work experience as a Data Scientist ideally in the renewable Energy field including in Solar;
Minimum of 3 years of experience with programming languages (Python strongly preferred; C#, R, MATLAB also relevant);
Demonstrated, practical experience with a variety of data science tools and techniques such as machine learning, neural networks, condition monitoring and pattern recognition;
Solid knowledge in statistics and mathematics;
Good understanding of machine learning and data mining algorithms;
Familiarity with large-scale data processing frameworks (eg. Apache Spark);
Demonstrated skill at data preprocessing, data modeling and data quality assessment (especially as related to time series data);
Demonstrated skill at using the right algorithms to analyze the data and provide meaningful insights;
Demonstrated skill in research ability for new algorithm development and deployment;
Demonstrated skill in feature extraction and real-time analytics development and deployment;
Ability to continuously learn and explore new techniques to provide insights and answers;
Critical thinking and problem-solving skills are a must;
Experience with cloud analytics engines a plus (e.g. Azure ML, Google TensorFlow, etc.) will be considered an asset;
Experience using version control (Git preferred) for collaborative code development will be considered an asset;
Experience developing analytics for product solutions is also considered an asset;
Availability to travel on occasions or as required (10% of the time approximately).


WHAT WE OFFER


Flexible core hours
Incentive pay and employee referral bonus programs
Employee recognition programs
Benefits coverage for you and your dependents
Fresh fruits, drinks and other snacks
Free parking and easy access to public transportation


